.TH "amdtp_am824_set_parameters" 9 "amdtp_am824_set_parameters" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdtp_am824_set_parameters \- set stream parameters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" amdtp_am824_set_parameters
.BI "(struct amdtp_stream *s "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rate "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pcm_channels "  ","
.BI "unsigned int midi_ports "  ","
.BI "bool double_pcm_frames "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "s" 12
the AMDTP stream to configure
.IP "rate" 12
the sample rate
.IP "pcm_channels" 12
the number of PCM samples in each data block, to be encoded
as AM824 multi-bit linear audio
.IP "midi_ports" 12
the number of MIDI ports (i.e., MPX-MIDI Data Channels)
.IP "double_pcm_frames" 12
one data block transfers two PCM frames
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The parameters must be set before the stream is started, and must not be
changed while the stream is running.
